ened the far right. Bringing Bakhtin into dialogue with key developments in contemporary politics, this book is a must-read for anyone interested in the Trump phenomenon, American politics, and populism.  aIssued also in print.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aThis eBook is made available Open Access under a CC BY-NC-ND 4.0 license: uhttps://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-nd/4.0  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 4aDemokratie. 4aPopulismus. 4aSocial Media. 4aTrump, Donald. 4aUSA. 7aPOLITICAL SCIENCE / American Government / General.2bisacsh  aDemocracy.  aPopulism.  aSocial Media.  aTrump, Donald.1 aGanesh, Bharath, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2023 Englishz978311131929208iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2023z9783111318912oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Education, Psychology, Comm 2023 Englishz978311131910008iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Education, Psychology, Communication 2023z9783111318141oZDB-23-SEW0 cEPUBz97831112422930 cprintz978311123799240uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9783111238135zOpen Access7040uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783111238135zOpen Access70423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9783111238135/original  a978-3-11-131910-0 EBOOK PACKAGE Education, Psychology, Comm 2023 Englishb2023  a978-3-11-131929-2 EBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2023 Englishb2023  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-DGGb2023  aZDB-23-GOA  aZDB-23-SEWb2023